<TITLE> Heavy arms fire erupts again at Peelkhana </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)Heavy gunfire broke out again at the BDR's Peelkhana Headquarters, an hour before an agreed deadline of 2pm Thursday for the mutinous border guards to lay down 'all arms'. bdnews24.com correspondents on the scene reported loud arms fire from around 1pm at Zigatola, Dhanmondi and Hazaribagh. Nearby residents and bystanders said they could hear machine gun fire erupting inside the complex. A meeting between a government delegation led by agriculture minister Matia Choudhury and the BDR mutineers appeared to reach an agreement on a deadline for 'total surrender'. Fazle Noor Taposh MP told reporters after the meeting, "The BDR rebels agreed to lay down all arms by 2pm." One of the group of rebel border guards said the same. bdnews24.c
